q "What is Capy?"
    a "A target-agnostic transpiler — your DSL, your output."
end

q "Does it handle \"quotes\" & <markup>?" open
    a "Yes. Captured prose is decoded then HTML-escaped, so \"quotes\" and <tags> render as text."
end

q "Can I omit the open/closed flag?"
    a "Yes — the trailing arg has a default of \"closed\"."
end
